{"title":"Tactic Racing debuts ultralight hubs weighing just 215g…for the set!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/tactic-racing-ultralight-hubs/","date":1639758064000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"exploded view of Tactic TR01 ultralight road and gravel bike hubs\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085016/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-1.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-281080\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The new Tactic Racing TR01 hubset comes in at just 215g for the set, which they claim is 50g lighter than DT Swiss’ 180s. An impressive feat, but something they say was 10 years in development and gives up nothing in terms of strength or performance.</p><p>In fact, with their patent-pending conical engagement rings, they say it offers extremely stiff, secure power transfer, and they’re both road- and gravel ready. Here’s how they did it…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3.jpg\" alt=\"Tactic TR01 ultralight road and gravel bike hubs\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1443\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3-297x238.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3-800x641.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3-120x96.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3-768x616.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085022/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-3-1536x1231.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>The hub shells are machined from an aerospace-grade aluminum alloy, which they say is stronger and lighter than standard alloys typically used for bicycle hubs. It takes a combined three hours to machine both hub shells, and the pics below show why.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of Tactic TR01 ultralight road and gravel bike hubs\" width=\"1400\" height=\"934\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085026/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-6-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>The hubs use a straight pull design and will launch with 24/24 and 28/28 spoke-count designs for front and rear, in Center Lock disc brake format. They’ll follow soon with rim brake models with 16/20/24 front and 24/28 rear spoke count options.</p><p>The hubs roll on ABEC 7 ceramic bearings with a Tungsten Disulfide low friction coating, which they say is used for extremely high performance applications, like the Mars Rover. Yes, this adds to their cost, and they’re not cheap…keep reading.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of Tactic TR01 ultralight road and gravel bike hubs\" width=\"1400\" height=\"934\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085033/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-9-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of Tactic TR01 ultralight road and gravel bike hubs\" width=\"1400\" height=\"934\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085031/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-8-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>Additional weight savings comes from machining away any excess material, though they say it’s pulled from areas that don’t reduce strength, stiffness, or durability. Despite the paltry weight, they say they’re ready for offroad (read: Gravel, Cyclocross) riding and racing, too.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of Tactic TR01 ultralight road and gravel bike hubs\" width=\"1400\" height=\"934\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085024/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-5-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>The result is a pair of hubs that come in at just 64g for the front and 151g for the rear, or 215g for the set. The rear hub shell barely wraps over the freehub body, showing how tight the package is, yet the insides look incredibly robust.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of Tactic TR01 ultralight hub freehub body engagement system\" width=\"1400\" height=\"934\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085019/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-2-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>The freehub body has a fixed, concave ring of teeth. Spring loaded inside the hub shell is its convex mate. They call this patent-pending design a ConicalFace Gear.</p><p>Besides offering nearly instant and full engagement of all 45 teeth, the conical design locks the parts into place in perfectly straight line. This adds rigidity to the system, minimizing any bending in the hub that could occur under high torsional loads from the drivetrain. While rare, and often very slight, typical ratchet-and-pawl systems can occasionally skip under extreme circumstances.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of Tactic TR01 ultralight hub freehub body engagement system\" width=\"1400\" height=\"934\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17085028/tactic-racing-TR01-hubs-7-freehub-bodies-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>At launch, they have XDR and 11/12sp HG freehub bodies, with Campagnolo versions coming soon. Here’s all that in bullet point form:</p><ul><li>45 point engagement</li><li>Shimano (11 and 12spd compatible), SRAM XDR, and Campagnolo freehub bodies</li><li>64g front, 151g rear for DISC BRAKE</li><li>100% mfg in Germany</li><li>24/24 and 28/28 available, and 16/20/24 F and 24/28R for rim brake soon.</li><li>ABEC 7 ceramic bearings with a Tungsten Disulfide low friction coating</li><li>ConicalFace Gear</li><li>Tested and raced by one of the world’s leading cycling teams</li></ul><p>Hubsets will retail for $1,300 USD ($1850 AUD / &nbsp;£1000 GBP / €1150 EUR) and start shipping January 1, 2022.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.tacticracing.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>TacticRacing.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"047ee0e73fd1b463f84a453bd3a47d95e3aff814976b05cb1d3493ff91e79011","category":"Cycling"}